#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:2
msgid "cd - change directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:7
msgid "cd [DIRECTORY]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:12
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:16
msgid ""
"NOTE: This page documents the fish builtin ``cd``. To see the documentation "
"on any non-fish versions, use ``command man cd``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:19
msgid "``cd`` changes the current working directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:21
msgid ""
"If *DIRECTORY* is given, it will become the new directory. If no parameter "
"is given, the :envvar:`HOME` environment variable will be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:23
msgid ""
"If *DIRECTORY* is a relative path, all the paths in the :envvar:`CDPATH` "
"will be tried as prefixes for it, in addition to :envvar:`PWD`. It is "
"recommended to keep **.** as the first element of :envvar:`CDPATH`, or :"
"envvar:`PWD` will be tried last."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:26
msgid ""
"Fish will also try to change directory if given a command that looks like a "
"directory (starting with **.**, **/** or **~**, or ending with **/**), "
"without explicitly requiring **cd**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:28
msgid ""
"Fish also ships a wrapper function around the builtin **cd** that "
"understands ``cd -`` as changing to the previous directory. See also :doc:"
"`prevd <prevd>`. This wrapper function maintains a history of the 25 most "
"recently visited directories in the ``$dirprev`` and ``$dirnext`` global "
"variables. If you make those universal variables your **cd** history is "
"shared among all fish instances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:33
msgid ""
"As a special case, ``cd .`` is equivalent to ``cd $PWD``, which is useful in "
"cases where a mountpoint has been recycled or a directory has been removed "
"and recreated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:35
msgid ""
"The **--help** or **-h** option displays help about using this command, and "
"does not change the directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:38
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/cd.rst:42
msgid ""
"cd\n"
"# changes the working directory to your home directory.\n"
"\n"
"cd /usr/src/fish-shell\n"
"# changes the working directory to /usr/src/fish-shell"
msgstr ""

